name: Abhishek Gill
review_text:
No words are enough to describe the beauty of this trail. From Kasol main market you need to take the metal bridge above the river to start the trail to Chalal village. It will take you around 45 mins to reach Chalal, but trust me you cannot complete it without breaks because there are many beautiful spots which will make you stop and admire the beauty of the nature for a while. The trek is alongside river and you will find many riverside cafes serving great local and Israeli food. This hike will take you through the beautiful views of river and some lush green trees. When you reach Chalal you can either relax at a cafe and head back to Kasol or you can choose a place to stay the night.
Recommended activities
Hiking, Walking

name: Akhil Raj
review_text:
If youre looking to immerse yourself in the stunning natural beauty of Himachal Pradesh, the trek from Kasol to Chalal Village is a must-experience adventure. The journey begins conveniently just after crossing the Kasol Bridge, where the excitement of trekking unfolds over a manageable distance of approx. 2 kms.

The pathway is well-paved, making it an inviting and accessible trek for both seasoned hikers and casual walkers. As you make your way alongside the enchanting Parvati River, you can't help but be captivated by the pristine scenery. The gentle sound of flowing water alongside the vibrant greenery creates a serene ambiance that is utterly refreshing. Its the perfect backdrop for capturing those Instagram-worthy moments or simply soaking in the tranquillity of nature.

Upon arrival in Chalal Village, you're greeted by an even denser blanket of greenery, which adds to the charm of this quaint destination. The villages lush surroundings make it an ideal spot to relax and reflect on the trek you've just completed.

One of the highlights of this trek is the abundance of small eateries dotted along the way. These charming little spots offer a variety of quick bites, allowing you to savor local flavors and recharge your energy. Whether you're in the mood for a warm cup of chai or some delicious snacks, you'll find something to satisfy your cravings.

However, a word of advice: don't forget to carry sufficient water with you. The trek, though short, can be demanding, particularly under the sun, and staying hydrated is crucial to ensure a pleasant experience.
Recommended activities
Hiking, Running, Dog Walking, Walking

name: Sai Sreerang
review_text:
The Chalal Trek is a short yet enchanting journey that starts right from the Kasol market and ends at the serene Chalal village. This trek, about 2 km long, is an easy walk that offers incredible natural beauty, making it perfect for beginners or anyone looking to unwind in nature. The trail runs alongside the mesmerizing Parvati River, which adds a continuous soundtrack of flowing water, creating a sense of calm and tranquility as you walk.

We stayed along the route at Wabi Sabi Hostel, right on the banks of the Parvati River. This location gave us direct access to the trek and made it easy to immerse ourselves in the peaceful surroundings. The cold climate of the region was perfect, offering a refreshing break from the heat of the cities. The trek is dotted with pine trees, and the mountains in the background add to the stunning landscape.

The sunsets and sunrises along the route are nothing short of magical. As the sun rises or sets behind the mountains, the entire sky lights up in shades of orange and pink, reflecting off the river and creating a breathtaking view that's worth the early wake-up or late stay.

Along the way, you'll encounter a few small settlements and cafes, where you can grab a bite or have a drink if you feel hungry or thirsty. The route is well-marked and frequented by locals, making it safe and easy to navigate. The people of Kasol are incredibly warm and welcoming, always ready with a smile or a helping hand, adding to the charm of the entire experience.

As you approach Chalal village, the trail opens up to reveal quaint wooden houses that transport you back in time, offering a glimpse into a simpler, more rustic way of life. In summary, the Chalal Trek is a must-do if you're in Kasol. Its manageable length, breathtaking views, and the serene atmosphere make it an experience that stays with you long after you've returned. Whether you're looking to explore the beauty of Himachal or just need a peaceful walk in nature, this trek is perfect for anyone.

Parking: You've to keep your vehicle at the Kasol market or before the bridge to start the trek.

Recommended activities
Hiking, Dog Walking, Walking

name: Mohit sharma
review_text:
Chalal Trek in Himachal Pradesh is an absolute must-do for anyone craving a thrilling adventure amidst breathtaking scenery. The trek offers a perfect blend of natural beauty, challenging trails, and cultural immersion. As you navigate through lush forests and meandering pathways, the views of the majestic Himalayas will leave you spellbound. The journey is not only about reaching the destination but also about the experiences along the way, from interacting with local villagers to enjoying serene moments by the riverside. Chalal Trek promises an unforgettable adventure for those seeking solace in natures embrace.

name: sanjay bora
review_text:
**Chalal Trek Trail Comprehensive Review:**

The Chalal Trek Trail is a captivating exploration through the enchanting Parvati Valley, promising trekkers a harmonious blend of natural beauty, cultural immersion, and a tranquil riverside experience. Heres a comprehensive overview, covering major points and essential conditions for this delightful trek:

**Trek Highlights:**
1. **Riverside Serenity:** The trail meanders along the picturesque Parvati River, offering a serene and soothing backdrop with the constant melody of flowing waters enhancing the overall trekking experience.
2. **Cultural Delight:** En route, trekkers encounter charming Himalayan villages like Chalal, providing opportunities to engage with locals, experience their culture, and witness the simplicity of mountain life.
3. **Lush Forests:** The trek takes you through verdant forests, creating a refreshing atmosphere and adding an element of biodiversity to the journey.

**Best Time to Visit:**
1. **Spring (March to May):** Ideal for witnessing the vibrant bloom of wildflowers, moderate temperatures, and a lively atmosphere as nature awakens.
2. **Autumn (September to November):** With clear skies, pleasant weather, and the added charm of autumn foliage, this period is perfect for both trekking and photography.

**Altitude:**
1. **Chalal Trek Altitude:** Ranging from approximately 1,500 meters to 2,000 meters (4,921 feet to 6,562 feet), the trek maintains a moderate elevation suitable for trekkers with varying fitness levels.

**Trekking Route:**
1. The journey typically begins from Kasol, a popular base for various treks in the Parvati Valley.
2. The trail leads to Chalal village, known for its tranquility and scenic beauty. Trekkers traverse riverside paths, cross charming bridges, and navigate through enchanting forests.
3. The trek can be extended to explore nearby destinations such as Tosh or Rasol, providing options for those seeking longer adventures.

**Major Points and Conditions:**
1. **Chalal Village:** A highlight of the trek, Chalal offers a serene setting by the riverside. Trekkers often take time to absorb the peaceful ambiance and interact with locals.
2. **Cafes and Culture:** The trail is dotted with cozy cafes, providing not only refreshments but also a chance to soak in the local and international backpacker culture. Each cafe adds its unique charm to the trek.
3. **Photography Opportunities:** From the scenic landscapes to vibrant village life, the trek offers abundant photography opportunities, making it a favorite among those with a passion for capturing the essence of the Himalayas.

**Key Tips for Trekkers:**
1. **Weather Preparedness:** Despite favorable seasons, Himalayan weather can be unpredictable. Trekkers should carry layers to adapt to temperature changes and be prepared for occasional rain.
2. **Responsible Trekking:** Given the cultural and ecological sensitivity of the region, trekkers are encouraged to follow Leave No Trace principles, respect local customs, and contribute to preserving the natural environment.

In conclusion, the Chalal Trek Trail is a tranquil and culturally rich journey, inviting trekkers to embrace the beauty of the Parvati Valley. Whether for a brief day trek or an extended exploration, this trek promises a harmonious union of nature, culture, and the joy of discovery.

name: Makhan Singh
review_text:
Chalal is one of the easiest treks you can take in Kasol. It takes around 30 minutes from Kasol to reach Chalal village. You can simply enjoy the beautiful view of the valley and the massive Parvati river while trekking to Chalal.Chalal hike starts from goSTOPS Kasol crossing the main market and Chalal bridge. The trek to Chalal village ends at Feedom cafe which is a 2 km long distance and takes around an hour to reach
Chalal, which draws millions of travellers worldwide, is notable for its trekking prospects. Surprisingly, this tiny hamlet will delight you with twice as much fun and excitement as any other trekking destination.
Being held at Oh Magical View Cafe, this Kasol New Year party will be lit up by booming DJ performances amidst the gigantic mountains of the valley
You begin this trek from Kasol. It will be a 45-50 minute walk from Kasol, where first you will discover the beautiful Chalal village. Great place all time. must try to visit
Scenic hiking route along the Parvati River passing through local villages with cafes along the way.limb up to an altitude of 7,900 feet on a trek to Chalal and Tosh. | Explore the magnificent beauty of mountains in the Parvati Valley. | Spend a night in tents pitched at the photogenic Once you are there, spend your mornings and evenings by strolling along the river to catch the most scenic views for a rewarding trip

name: Amrik Saha
review_text: While Kasol gets the spotlight amongst the villages of the Parvati Valley, one can enjoy the true serenity of the magical Himachal Pradesh by trekking a little further from this major town to the quaint little village of Chalal. Situated at an altitude of over 5300 feet and a 30-minute trek away from the tourist hub of Kasol, Chalal has managed to retain its old-world mountain village rustic charm. Set in the beautiful Parvati Valley of the Himalayas, with a grand view of snow-capped mountains and majestic pine trees, this quaint town has been nicknamed the Isreal of Himachal Pradesh, and rightfully so!

name: TABISH AYUBI
review_text:
Come to see the beautiful Chalal.
An iron bridge connects Chalal to Kasol.

Its almost a walk of 1.5-2 km alongside the beautiful Parvati river. You can find a few chai tapris, a couple of houses with few shops. You can sit for a bonfire in any of those shops during the evening.

The vibe is just beautiful and pahadis are just Lovable beings. They love dogs.

You can go for a Trek early in the morning or in the evening to get a better view coz in the sun you may get tired.

Chalal is very small and very beautifully settled alongside the Parvati river. If you are visiting Kasol, then You must walk towards Chalal too.

name: Aman
review_text:
If you are looking to escape the crowd of Kasol, the charming village of Chalal is your ideal destination. As mentioned above, Chalal is quite isolated as many tourists head to Tosh and Kheerganga from Kasol. Therefore, people seeking solitude in the lap of nature are most welcome to have their desire fulfilled in Chalal.
Once you get your eyes off the beautiful, chirpy birds perching on the colourful tree branches, the yummy local and Israeli food of Chalal would thrill you. Cafes and eateries serve fresh food at budgeted rates. So, dig in and let your thoughts flow as the free-flowing waters of the nearby Parvati River.

name: Anindita Goswami
review_text:
Depressing. Why?

1. Temp feels like 42. The entire trek though short was burning hot and sweaty.
2. The view is really average. Jibhi and towards bahu is same or better from my perspective.
3. The entire route has garbage and plastics of all sprawled everywhere. How can one enjoy the beautiful gushing Parvati river with human destruction all around.
4. This place belongs to younger crowds collage teens hippies who basically enjoy when them come in groups or backpacking definitely not a true nature lover like me who likes peace and isolation from the crowd.

I am glad I didnt trek with my luggage and I returned in anhour and Im not staying at the homestays in chalal.

Honestly I wish I could spread a public word around to draw attention to the garbage people are building at this natures place. Locals should intervene and clean the place and then only tourist will behave.

name: Mo Shahid
review_text:
What they say about Kasol is real. The trail to chalal village is a wonderful experience.
It is 1 hour trek and complete trek and following things one can experience just take 5-6 hours.
The beauty of chalal trek starts when you leave kasol and gets on other side of river crossing a foot bridge.
At bridge you can witness the some beautiful mountain peaks.
Under the bridge there is a hot water spring. You should really take a bath when u come back after finishing chalal trek . The hot water spring will take a good care of your tiredness.
So talking about chalal trek if you are a dog lover dont think twice to go on this trek. On the mid of trekking u will find some such good boi ( dogs ) they are too friendly and in case if u forgets the way just follow them. You will trek along side river which is a really good experience once you reach chalal have some Maggi and chai.

name: Anant Garg
review_text: Chalal trek is a very small trek of around 4km but is quite beautiful. The walk alongside Parvati river is very refreshing and the sound of the river is music to the ears. It is a half day roundtrip trek. It is not difficult at all but only a test of stamina. More importantly it is a kind of warm up if you are planning for Kheerganga trek the following day. One can sit and relax at the banks of Parvati river during the trek. Just close your eyes to feel the cool breeze hitting on your face and giving a calming and soothing effect. This same trek can also be done at night. Walking alongside a river in the woods under the moonlight can be a great experience. However the place becomes secluded and scary at night with no one around. So carry torches if you are planning to do it.

Quite extensively used trek trail from kasol city center to chalal. One can find lots of camps/stays along the trek. The way is along the river with rocky and muddy trail. Better to have good trekking shoes for a comfortable trek.
Compared to other parts of kasol and its neighborhood this one is pretty comfortable and safe for first timers.

name: Nisarg J
review_text: Locals would say that its just a fifteen minutes walk from kasol to chalaal. But let me break the myth, the actual time for the Trek from kasol to chalaal is about 40-45 minutes. The trek is comfortable and not so steep, its just a 40 minute walk. You will encounter peddlers selling stuff on the path. Food in chalaal is relatively expensive and ok compared to kasol, but stay in chalaal is cheaper compared to kasol, in the range of rs 800 to 1200 per room of 2 in june19. Prefer to have your stay in chalaal and have your food at kasol Shankar dhaba.

name: Akhil Singh
review_text: If youre visiting Kasol and are there for multiple days then often you will find yourself having nothing to do more. This trek is a relatively easier trek and I would recommend every visitor for taking it. There will be many spots where you can sit on gigantic stones very close to the river and enjoy the peace. Also this trek is famous for Hash peddlers whom you will find very frequently while walking. Beware of scams though i.e. dont ever pay the money in advance. Personally I think its one of the very things you can do in Kasol. If you are here for more number of days or want more adventure then go to Tosh as it is way higher than Kasol and offers stunning view of snow laden mountains.

review_text: Kasol.....in ... Kullu , paradise on Earth ...where clouds daily descends to kiss the loafty mountain... review_text:
Its a moderately easy trek, which tests your determination right at the end with steep climbs and wet trails. The governing bodies are doing a good job at keeping the trail safe.
Its a 3 hour long trek along a valley that leads to Rasol village. Its trail is used by a lot of people who travel daily, they will guide you during the trek. The trek also has arrows that help you with directions.
The first halt stop is halfway through to the trek, so be prepared for it.

name: Krishna Jaiswal
review_text:
Chalal is a tiny village near Kasol. Feel welcomed as you are greeted by the majestic mountains, sounds of the gushing river, chirping of birds, and long stretches of Marijuana fields. By the way, Marijuana cultivation is a prime occupation of the villagers of Chalal. Apart from Weed cultivation, Chalal is also known for its trance and psychedelic parties.

Walk for a short while to arrive at the campsite. Settle by the riverside and enjoy the greenery around. Relax for a while and relish a delicious breakfast served to you. Once you feel refreshed, get set for an exciting trekking time. As you walk through the lanes of Kasol towards Chalal, witness the numerous Israeli cafes and shops. If interested, you might as well purchase your souvenirs from here. Continue walking towards Chalal, quite popular for its trance and psychedelic parties. This trek, from Kasol to Chalal, is a short one and will last for about 2 hours, with short halts in between.

Later in the evening, you must return to the campsite. Have fun as you relax around a bonfire and enjoy dancing and singing with your companions

Weather: Summer 15degC to 25degC Winter 2degC to 15degC

review_text:
Chalal trail is a small 2.5-3km, 45-50 mins trek along the bank of river Parvat, right in the middle of Kasol. The trek passes through the dense forest and takes you to the famous Tripping Forrest cafe. If you are looking for a little lone time, then its a perfect evening outing place.

You will find a lot of cafes along the way. The post sunset view of the river is breath taking and if you are a photographer, then you can click some awesome photographs here. And not to forget, people can get themselves clicked with river, mountain and deep blue sky in the background.

name: Sharanya Gupta
review_text:
Chalal is THE place to be if youre in or around Kasol. Located at a comfortable 10-15min walk away from Kasol, Chalal is the ideal place to stay if you want to stay around Kasol, but want to avoid the hustle bustle and maddening crowd of Kasol. The room rates around this place are reasonable and much cheaper compared to Kasol. This village is located on the valley by the Parvati river, so, you might not get the views you might be looking for. But, the green hills around, and the pine lines, makes it an amazing place to sit and ponder.

Chalal is also the base point for the hike to Rasol. It takes 3-4hours to reach Rasol from Chalal, depending on your speed and stamina. Happy travelling.

name: Priyanshu Yadav
review_text:
While Kasol gets the spotlight amongst the villages of the Parvati Valley, one can enjoy the true serenity of the magical Himachal Pradesh by trekking a little further from this major town to the quaint little village of Chalal. Situated at an altitude of over 5300 feet and a 30-minute trek away from the tourist hub of Kasol, Chalal has managed to retain its old world mountain village rustic charm, set in the beautiful Parvati Valley of the Himalayas, with a grand view of snow-capped mountains and majestic pine trees.

With Kasol becoming a mainstream village, Chalal has found its fan following among backpackers and trekkers, who come out here to trek, camp out under the stars, or enjoy some hot chai as they soak in the sheer splendour of the scenic panorama of the grand Himalayas. The large number of backpackers and tourists that visit the place have given rise to a number of parties that happen deep in the forests, forming the ideal spot nestled within the mountains under a mystical sky full of stars that no other place on the planet could ever come close to offering. However, the delight of losing yourself in the glory of the mountains and living the simple life still remains within the tiny hamlet of Chalal, making it a beautiful essential for backpackers across the globe

A light trek/trail to the village of Chalal, it promises many scenic views along the bank of the river and a look at the life in a hill top village. Dotted by greenery towards the mid section, theres enough of blue, green and the myriad hues of nature (in spring).

Pro-tip: No hiking equipment required, youll do great with just sports shoes.

name: Pankaj Khatri
review_text: It is a riverside trail starting behind Punjtara. After crossing the bridge above Parvati river it takes us to Chalal village. Away from the roads and vehicles and city noise and polluted air, it is a scenic and peaceful place to live. My friends and I started this trail at night with mobile torches in our hands and no more than 10 feet was visible at any time. It was a 20 minute trail for us to reach Om Himalayan Camp and after the first time we were surefooted at every step. Wear sports shoes for better grip to avoid slipping on the marbles.

review_text: If you ever been to kasol, just go to Chalal. The payment is besides the river with smooth cold breeze. People who went with children or elders and people who cant do 3-4 km trekking, Chalal is the place to go. Obviously the place is infamous for black gold, but its worth been there at least for once. Better than Manali.

name: Yash Kumar
review_text: The chalal trek trail starts from this bridge which stands on parvati river in parvati valley. Its hardly 100 metres away from the bus stop of Kasol. Right along the trail, there is this beautiful parvati valley, loosen up your shoes pit your feet into it and relax, one can easily sit whole day here. The sound of the river smashing the larger stones and the clarity and the purity of the water is absolutely mesmerizing.. The trail is simple walk and very easy takes around 40 minutes (with ni stop) to reach the chalal village. There is nothing to view from the village. But yes, there are few cafes along the way, so guys can chill and spend some time in peace.

name: Rahul Yadav
review_text: As a trekking enthusiast, you would love each and every bit of your experience in Chalal Trek Trail. The trail is enriched with numerous natural beauties. The mountainous location is picturesque because of the appropriate setting of rivers, forest areas and occasional villages. Those who trek here, never forget the mesmerising beauty of the River Parvati.

name: shubham dhikale
review_text:
Words will fall short while you speak about the never ending beauty of this place. And if you are planning for an offbeat wilderness then this is the perfect destination for you. A destination offered with the greater part of nature's gifts, Kasol is known for its Israeli occupants, Parvati waterway, trekking base-camp and Malana. Kasol is a town in Himachal Pradesh, northern India.

Known as the center point of substantial number of Israelis, this remote region with its energetic bistros and alcohol distributes mixes the Indian and non-Indian society with flawlessness. This is a must visit place for you

name: Deepamay Jana
review_text: It was our first real trek as a group of 8 and believe you me..the uphill climb was not all easy. The distance might be just 3 KMS from Kasol to Rasol but for an amateur it will take around 5 hours with frequent stops due to heavy luggage.The real challenge will begin after you reach a cafe( just a tea Maggie joint) ,the climb gets tougher when you cross this locality. Ideal time to start would be around 10 in the morning from Kasol.Carry sufficient water,hash and munchies.

name: Nikhil Rathi
review_text: Right after the small bridge in Kasol youll find a small trail in between 2 cafes on your left when you are walking facing the road towards Manikaran. After around 20 average steps youll start decending on the uneven path which sort of enters the forest. That is the start of Chalal trek Trail. Not difficult, manageable by everyone. Just a 2-4km trek all along the river. Its beautiful, and peaceful.
